content.description: Left of Back Door Man is an overhanging, obtuse corner with small roof and crux slab at the top. Pure problem of stemming, liebacking, a mini roof and hard slab, a classic.
content.location: Just left, 6 m, of Back Door Man.

climbs.fa: unknown, but led, free soloed in 1980's

content.description: Overhanging hand and lieback crack, unique for area.
content.protection: Hand size cams, or top rope or pads after practice.
content.location: Obvious crack at North Face Crags, Vaso Island, MD. Directly across from The Dream at Carderock. Very unique for area. Can easily be seen from Stannards Playground/TB Boulder in winter.

content.description:
North Facing, overhanging crags, directly across Potomac River braid from Carderocks Jungle Cliff, Dream, Impossible Block. Shist, steep, shady with important and unique climbs for the area.

 Backdoor Man and I Guess, I Just Don't Know are 2 classics on the largest, steepest crag, but there are other shorter routes on outlying cliffs like the 5.9 bombay groove to the west.
